<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbfc320b1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s13455"><num value="13455">§ 13455.</num><heading> Electric drives</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbfc320b2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s13455/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Program</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall conduct a 5-year program, in accordance with sections 13541 and 13542 of this title, to increase the efficiency of electric drive technologies, including adjustable speed drives, high speed motors, and high efficiency motors.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbfc320b3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s13455/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Proposals</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Within 1 year after <date date="1992-10-24">October 24, 1992</date>, the Secretary shall solicit proposals for projects under this section.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idbfc320b4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/102/486/tXXI/s2105">Pub. L. 102–486, title XXI, § 2105</ref>, <date date="1992-10-24">Oct. 24, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/3070">106 Stat. 3070</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
